    <thetext>Description of problem:
When you install KDM with &quot;dnf install kdm&quot; you will also get &quot;kdm-settings&quot; which contains

/etc/kde/kdm/kdmrc:Theme=/usr/share/kde4/apps/kdm/themes/F23

BUT you do not get /usr/share/kde4/apps/kdm/themes/F23 which is part of f23-kdm-theme which is not installed by default or by dependency.

So KDM does not start, but shows an error dialog about the above file missing.

Version-Release number of selected component (if applicable):
kde-workspace-4.11.22-13.fc24

How reproducible:
always

Steps to Reproduce:
1. dnf install kdm
2. systemctl disable gdm ; systemctl disable sddm
3. systemctl enable kdm
4. reboot

Actual results:
An error dialog of KDM saying: /usr/share/kde4/apps/kdm/themes/F23 not found

Expected results:
KDM working

Additional info:</thetext>
